B. Equivalence Discussion between Detection and Grounding
B. 检测与定位之间的等价性讨论

In Section 3.1 of the main paper, we discussed the equivalence between detection and grounding. We corroborate the discussion with empirical experiments.
在主论文的第3.1节中，我们讨论了检测与定位之间的等价性。我们通过实证实验证实了这一讨论。
When all object categories fit into a single prompt. We first confirm that when all categories fit into one prompt, our grounding formulation is equivalent to classical object detection. We conduct the experiments on COCO [6]. We first choose the SoTA detection model Dynamic Head (Dy-Head) [2] based on the Swin-Tiny Transformer backbone [7] as the base object detection mode. We then transform this model into a grounding model as described in Section 3.1: we concatenate the 80 class names with "." into one prompt and replace DyHead's classification loss with our grounding loss. We use BERT (base-uncased) [3] to encode the text prompt. When concatenating the class names, we follow a fixed order.
当所有对象类别都适合单个提示时。我们首先确认，当所有类别都适合一个提示时，我们的定位公式与经典对象检测等价。我们在COCO [6]上进行实验。我们首先选择基于Swin-Tiny Transformer骨干网络[7]的Dynamic Head (Dy-Head) [2]作为基础对象检测模型。然后，我们按照第3.1节中描述的将此模型转换为定位模型：我们将80个类名与"."连接成一个提示，并将DyHead的分类损失替换为我们的定位损失。我们使用BERT (base-uncased) [3]来编码文本提示。在连接类名时，我们遵循一个固定顺序。
We train the two models with the exact same hyperpa-rameters as in [2]: we train with the standard 2x training configurations [4]. We train with batch size 32 and learning rate 1×10−4 (for the model with grounding reformulation, we use 1×10−5 for the BERT text encoder). We decay the learning rate at 67% and 89% of the total training steps.
我们使用与 [2] 中完全相同的超参数训练两个模型：我们使用标准 2x 训练配置 [4] 进行训练。我们使用批量大小为 32 和学习率 1×10−4（对于带有定位重写的模型，我们对 BERT 文本编码器使用 1×10−5）。我们在总训练步数的 67% 和 89% 处衰减学习率。
The two models achieve the same performance on COCO 2017val: 49.4 AP. Their results are close to the 49.7 reported in the last row of Table 6 of Dai et al. [2] (the small difference is presumably due to the implementation difference). Thus, we conclude that when all categories can fit into a single prompt, grounding and detection tasks are equivalent.
两个模型在 COCO 2017val 上的性能相同：49.4 AP。它们的结果与 Dai 等人 [2] 表格 6 最后一行报告的 49.7 相近（小的差异可能是由于实现差异造成的）。因此，我们得出结论，当所有类别都能适应单个提示时，定位和检测任务是等价的。
When not all object categories can fit into a single prompt. The text encoder for the prompt has a limit on the input sentence length. For example, BERT can only encode sentences containing at most 512 tokens. In our implementation, to reduce computational costs, we limit the input length to 256 . Thus, for certain datasets with a large vocabulary (e.g., Objects 365 [8] has 365 object categories), we cannot fit all category names into one prompt. As a practical solution, we can split the category names into multiple prompts, during both training time and inference time. We
当不是所有对象类别都能适应单个提示时。提示的文本编码器对输入句子长度有限制。例如，BERT 只能编码最多包含 512 个标记的句子。在我们的实现中，为了降低计算成本，我们将输入长度限制为 256。因此，对于具有大量词汇的某些数据集（例如，Objects 365 [8] 有 365 个对象类别），我们无法将所有类别名称放入一个提示中。作为一种实际解决方案，我们可以在训练时间和推理时间将类别名称拆分为多个提示。

C. Transfer to Established Benchmarks
C. 转移到已建立的基准

We introduce the implementation details of the models used in Section 4 and discuss the difference between public image-text data and the data crawled by us.
我们介绍了第4节中使用的模型的实现细节，并讨论了公共图像-文本数据与我们抓取的数据之间的差异。

C.1. Pre-training Details
C.1. 预训练细节

In Section 4, we introduced GLIP-T (A), GLIP-T (B), GLIP-T (B), GLIP-T (C), GLIP-T, and GLIP-L. We introduce the implementation details in the following. We pre-train models based on Swin-Tiny models with 32 GPUs and a batch size of 64 , and models based on Swin-Large with 64 GPUs and a batch size of 64 . We use a base learning rate of 1×10−5 for the language backbone and 1×10−4 for all other parameters. The learning rate is stepped down by a factor of 0.1 at the 67% and 89% of the total training steps. We decay the learning rate when the zero-shot performance on COCO saturates. The max input length is 256 tokens for all models.
在第4节中，我们介绍了GLIP-T (A)、GLIP-T (B)、GLIP-T (B)、GLIP-T (C)、GLIP-T和GLIP-L。我们在以下内容中介绍实现的细节。我们基于Swin-Tiny模型使用32个GPU和批次大小为64进行预训练，基于Swin-Large模型使用64个GPU和批次大小为64进行预训练。对于语言主干网络，我们使用基础学习率1×10−5，对于所有其他参数，我们使用1×10−4。在学习步骤的67%和89%时，学习率会以0.1的因子递减。当在COCO上的零样本性能饱和时，我们会衰减学习率。所有模型的最大输入长度为256个token。
Prompt design for detection data. As noted in Section B, when we pre-train on datasets such as Objects 365, we cannot fit all categories into one prompt. During pretraining, we randomly down-sample the categories and keep only the down-sampled categories in the prompt. We randomly shuffle the categories' order in the prompt. If a positive category is discarded and not kept in the prompt after down-sampling, we will also drop its corresponding boxes from the box labels.
检测数据的提示设计。如B节所述，当我们在Objects 365等数据集上进行预训练时，我们无法将所有类别放入一个提示中。在预训练期间，我们随机下采样类别，并在提示中仅保留下采样的类别。我们随机打乱提示中类别的顺序。如果在下采样后，一个正类别被丢弃并且没有保留在提示中，我们也将从框标签中删除其对应的框。
The down-sampling is done randomly on the fly for each training example and serves as data augmentation. Specifically, for an example, we denote the positive classes that appear in the image as Cpos  and the rest negative classes as Cneg.  With a probability of 0.05,we sample one positive category from Cpos  ; with a probability of 0.05,we sample one negative category from Cneg  ; with a probability of 0.5, we keep all of Cpos  and sample from Cneg  till we have 85 categories in the prompt. For the rest of the time, we uniformly choose a number N from 1-85 and put N categories in the prompt; we always prioritize positive categories; but with a probability of 0.2 , we might drop some positive categories from the prompt.
随机下采样在每次训练示例中即时进行，作为数据增强。具体来说，对于某个示例，我们将图像中出现的正类别标记为 Cpos ，其余的负类别标记为 Cneg. 。以0.05的概率，我们从 Cpos  中抽取一个正类别；以0.05的概率，我们从 Cneg  中抽取一个负类别；以0.5的概率，我们保留所有的 Cpos  并从 Cneg  中抽取，直到提示中包含85个类别。其余时间，我们均匀地从1-85中选择一个数字 N，并在提示中放置 N 个类别；我们总是优先考虑正类别；但是以0.2的概率，我们可能会从提示中删除一些正类别。
Augmentation for image-text data with generated boxes.
对于生成框的图像-文本数据的增强。
When we pre-train the model on image-text data with generated boxes, we find it beneficial to increase the difficulty. We mix a few negative captions (that are from other examples and do not match with the image) with the positive caption (that is matched to the image) to form a longer text input. The model is trained to predict boxes and align them to the correct phrases in the positive caption. The model would need to first identify the positive caption among a few potential captions and then align the box to the correct phrases in the positive caption. This makes the grounding task more challenging and help the model learn a semantic-rich representation during pre-training. This augmentation is also done randomly on the fly. For each training example, with a probability of 0.3 , we conduct such augmentation and mix in 19 negative captions; with a probability of 0.3 , we mix in a random number (uniformly drawn between 1-19) of negative captions; for the rest of the time, we do not conduct such augmentation.
当我们在带有生成框的图像-文本数据上预训练模型时，我们发现增加难度是有益的。我们将一些负样本标题（来自其他示例且与图像不匹配）与正样本标题（与图像匹配）混合，形成一个更长的文本输入。模型被训练用于预测框并将它们与正样本标题中的正确短语对齐。模型需要首先在几个潜在的标题中识别出正样本标题，然后将框与正样本标题中的正确短语对齐。这使得定位任务更具挑战性，并帮助模型在预训练期间学习到语义丰富的表示。这种增强也是随机即时进行的。对于每个训练示例，我们有30%的概率进行此类增强并混合19个负样本标题；有30%的概率混合一个随机数量（均匀分布在1-19之间）的负样本标题；其余时间则不进行此类增强。

C.2. Evaluation Details
C.2. 评估细节

For fine-tuning on COCO, we use a base learning rate of 1×10−5 for pre-trained models.
在COCO上进行微调时，我们对预训练模型使用基础学习率 1×10−5。
For zero-shot evaluation on LVIS, since LVIS has over 1,000 categories and they cannot be fit into one text prompt, we segment them into multiple chunks, fitting 40 categories into one prompt and query the model multiple times with the different prompts. We find that models tend to overfit on LVIS during the course of pre-training so we monitor the performance on minival for all models and report the results with the best checkpoints.
对于在LVIS上进行零样本评估，由于LVIS有超过1000个类别，它们无法适应一个文本提示，我们将它们分割成多个块，每个提示适应40个类别，并使用不同的提示多次查询模型。我们发现，在预训练过程中，模型往往会在LVIS上过拟合，因此我们监控所有模型在minival上的性能，并使用最佳检查点报告结果。
For zero-shot evaluation on Flickr 30K ,models may also overfit during the course of pre-training so we monitor the performance on the validation set for all models and report the results with the best checkpoints.
对于在Flickr 30K 上进行零样本评估，模型在预训练过程中也可能过拟合，因此我们监控所有模型在验证集上的性能，并使用最佳检查点报告结果。

C. 3. Difference Between Public Data and Web- Crawled Data
C. 3. 公共数据与网络爬取数据的差异

For GLIP-T pre-trained with image-text data, as mentioned in Section 4, we train two versions, one with public data (CC3M,SBU) and another with data we crawled (Cap4M). Here we provide a comparison between the two models in Table 1.
对于在图像-文本数据上预训练的GLIP-T，如第4节所述，我们训练了两个版本，一个使用公共数据（CC3M、SBU），另一个使用我们抓取的数据（Cap4M）。在这里，我们在表1中提供了这两个模型的对比。
The two models differ only slightly, with the Cap4M version better on LVIS while the CC3M+SBU version better on COCO. We conjecture that this is potentially because the public data is more extensively screened and contains more common categories and less rare concepts. Thus it performs slightly better on COCO while lags slightly on LVIS.
两个模型之间的差异很小，Cap4M版本在LVIS上的表现更好，而CC3M+SBU版本在COCO上的表现更好。我们推测，这可能是由于公共数据经过了更广泛的筛选，包含更多常见类别和较少的罕见概念。因此，它在COCO上的表现略好，而在LVIS上稍显不足。

D. Computation Cost and Performance Analy- sis of Deep Fusion
D. 深度融合的计算成本与性能分析

In this section, we provide a more detailed ablation on the computational cost and performance effect of the language-aware deep fusion proposed in Section 3.
在这一节中，我们对第3节中提出的语言感知深度融合的计算成本和性能效果进行了更详细的消融研究。

D.1. Computational Cost
D.1. 计算成本

We test the additional computational cost of the language-aware deep fusion for both GLIP-T and GLIP-L. For inference, we test on a P100 GPU with batch size 1 . Note that for inference with GLIP without deep fusion, we could cache the language embeddings of the prompts; thus the inference time of GLIP without deep fusion is equivalent to that of DyHead [2].
我们测试了语言感知深度融合对GLIP-T和GLIP-L的额外计算成本。对于推理，我们在P100 GPU上以批量大小1进行测试。请注意，对于没有深度融合的GLIP进行推理时，我们可以缓存提示的语言嵌入；因此，没有深度融合的GLIP的推理时间与DyHead [2]相当。
For training, we test on a standard DGX-2 machine with 16V100GPUs (we test under the multi-GPU setting as it mimics the actual training environment): for GLIP-T models, we use 2 images per batch and for GLIP-L models, we use 1 images per batch. As the fusion module in-vovles multi-head attention over a large number of input elements,we turn on gradient checkpointing 1 for the deep fusion module, which increases training time but reduces GPU memory consumption.
为了训练，我们在标准的DGX-2机器上进行了测试，配备了16V100GPUs（我们测试了多GPU设置，因为它模拟了实际的训练环境）：对于GLIP-T模型，我们每个批次使用2张图像，而对于GLIP-L模型，我们每个批次使用1张图像。由于融合模块涉及对大量输入元素的多头注意力，我们为深度融合模块启用了梯度检查点1，这增加了训练时间但减少了GPU内存消耗。
Table 2 shows that the language-aware deep fusion brings less than 1x additional computational cost overall.
表2显示，语言感知的深度融合整体上带来的额外计算成本不到1x。

D.2. Performance
D.2. 性能

We provide an analysis on the effect of language-aware deep fusion when different kinds of pre-training data are used. We pre-train four variants of GLIP-T and show the results In Table 3. Deep fusion is beneficial for testing on 1) common categories (i.e., COCO); 2) grounding tasks (i.e., Flickr30K), and 3) low-resource transfer to real-world downstream tasks (i.e., ODinW).
我们分析了在不同种类的预训练数据使用时，语言感知深度融合的效果。我们预训练了GLIP-T的四个变体，并在表3中展示了结果。深度融合对于以下测试是有益的：1）常见类别（即COCO）；2）定位任务（即Flickr30K）；3）面向现实世界下游任务的低资源迁移（即ODinW）。
However, on LVIS, the effect of deep fusion seems unclear: when only detection data are used, deep fusion seems to degrades performance (row 1 v.s. row 2); when grounding data are present, deep fusion degrades common category performance but improves rare category performance. Our assumption is that when GLIP is only trained with detection data (e.g., O365), the language model could "overfit" to the categories in O365 and does not generalize to novel categories well (i.e., outputs out-of-distribution text representation). The deep fusion could "amplify" such overfit as the visual representation is conditioned on the language model. Thus, when tested on prompts containing novel categories (e.g., LVIS), deep fusion could degrade performance. When grounding data are used, such overfit could be mitigated.
然而，在LVIS上，深度融合的效果似乎并不明确：当仅使用检测数据时，深度融合似乎会降低性能（第1行与第2行相比）；当有定位数据时，深度融合会降低常见类别的性能，但提高了稀有类别的性能。我们的假设是，当GLIP只通过检测数据（例如O365）进行训练时，语言模型可能会“过拟合”O365中的类别，并且不能很好地泛化到新颖类别（即输出超出分布的文本表示）。深度融合可能会“放大”这种过拟合，因为视觉表示是基于语言模型的。因此，当在包含新颖类别（例如LVIS）的提示上进行测试时，深度融合可能会降低性能。当使用定位数据时，这种过拟合可能会得到缓解。

E. Object Detection in the Wild
E. 野外物体检测

In this section, we provide the details and additional results for the experiments in Section 5.
在这一节中，我们提供了第5节中实验的详细信息和额外结果。

E.1. Dataset Details
E.1. 数据集细节

We use 13 datasets from Roboflow 2 . Roboflow hosts over 30 datasets and we exclude datasets that are too challenging (e.g., detecting different kinds of chess pieces) or impossible to solve without specific domain knowledge (e.g., understanding sign language).
我们使用了Roboflow 2 的13个数据集。Roboflow托管了超过30个数据集，我们排除了那些过于具有挑战性的数据集（例如，检测不同种类的棋子）或没有特定领域知识无法解决的数据集（例如，理解手语）。
We provide the details of the 13 datasets we use in Table 4. We include the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset as a reference dataset, as public baselines have been established on this dataset. For PascalVOC, we follow the convention and report on validation set. For Pistols, there are no official validation or test sets so we split the dataset ourselves.
我们在表4中提供了我们使用的13个数据集的详细信息。我们包含PASCAL VOC 2012数据集作为参考数据集，因为在该数据集上已经建立了公共基线。对于PascalVOC，我们遵循惯例，在验证集上报告结果。对于Pistols数据集，没有官方的验证集或测试集，所以我们自己分割了数据集。

E.2. Manual Prompt Tuning
E.2. 手动提示调整

As discussed in Section 5, we find it beneficial to manually design some prompts to provide language guidance. We provide the prompts we use in Table 5. We design the prompts for 6 datasets. Since some prompts are sentences, we only apply these prompts for models trained with grounding data (GLIP-T (C), GLIP-T, and GLIP-L). For GLIP-T (A) and GLIP-T (B), we find it beneficial to use prompts for the Rabbits and Mushrooms datasets, as the prompts there are just single word or short phrases. Overall, using prompts improves AP without any model re-training (e.g., the AP improves from 22.1 to 50.0 for EgoHands).
如第5节所述，我们发现手动设计一些提示以提供语言指导是有益的。我们在表5中提供了我们使用的提示。我们为6个数据集设计了提示。由于一些提示是句子，我们只将这些提示应用于使用定位数据（GLIP-T (C)、GLIP-T和GLIP-L）训练的模型。对于GLIP-T (A)和GLIP-T (B)，我们发现对于Rabbits和Mushrooms数据集使用提示是有益的，因为那里的提示只是一个单词或短句。总的来说，使用提示可以在不进行任何模型重新训练的情况下提高AP（例如，EgoHands的AP从22.1提高到50.0）。

E.4. One Model for All Tasks
E.4. 一个模型适用于所有任务

In Section 5.2, we conduct experiments with respect to deployment efficiency: tuning the least amount of parameters for the best performance. For all models, we experiment with the linear probing setting; for GLIP models, we also experiment with the prompt tuning setting. For linear probing, we try both the vanilla approach (simply tune the classification and localization head) and the cosine scale approach [9]. Below we provide the implementation details.
在5.2节中，我们进行了关于部署效率的实验：调整最小数量的参数以获得最佳性能。对于所有模型，我们在线性探针设置下进行实验；对于GLIP模型，我们还尝试了提示调整设置。对于线性探针，我们尝试了标准方法（仅调整分类和定位头）和余弦缩放方法[9]。下面我们提供实现细节。
For the vanilla linear probing, we train with a learning rate of 1×10−4 ,batch size of 4,and weight decay of 0.05 . For linear probing with the cosine scale, we use a scale of 20.0 per suggestions of Wang et al. [9], learning rate of 0.01, batch size of 4 , and weight decay of 0.05 . For prompt tuning, we train with a learning rate of 0.05 , batch size of 4 , and weight decay of 0.25 . We have conducted preliminary searches for the hyper-parameters.
对于标准线性探针，我们以1×10−4的学习率，4的批量大小和0.05的权重衰减进行训练。对于使用余弦缩放的线性探针，我们根据Wang等人[9]的建议使用20.0的缩放，学习率为0.01，批量大小为4，权重衰减为0.05。对于提示调整，我们以0.05的学习率，4的批量大小和0.25的权重衰减进行训练。我们已经对超参数进行了初步搜索。
Results are present in Table 7 (linear probing) and Table 8 (prompt tuning). Comparing them with full-tuning results (Table 6), we see prompt tuning performance of GLIP is competitive, showing the deployment efficiency. Contrary to Wang etal . [9] who report that linear probing can deliver competitive performance for classical detection models, we find that linear probing does not work well compared to full tuning. We find that the reason could be the transfer datasets (ODinW) in our case contain a lot of novel tasks and domains, while experiments in Wang et al. focus on transferring to common domains (e.g., PascalVOC and COCO). In Table 10, we report the per-dataset performance. We find that for some common tasks or domains (e.g., PascalVOC and Vehicles), linear probing of DyHead COCO performs competitively with full fine-tuning but the gap is large for some other tasks of a novel domain (e.g., AerialDrone).
结果呈现于表7（线性探测）和表8（即时调整）。与全调整结果（表6）相比，我们看到GLIP的即时调整性能具有竞争力，显示出部署效率。与王等人 etal 的报告 [9] 相反，他们指出线性探测可以为经典检测模型提供有竞争力的性能，我们发现与全调整相比，线性探测效果不佳。我们认为原因可能是我们案例中的迁移数据集（ODinW）包含了许多新颖的任务和领域，而王等人进行的实验主要集中在迁移到常见领域（例如，PascalVOC和COCO）。在表10中，我们报告了每个数据集的性能。我们发现对于一些常见任务或领域（例如，PascalVOC和车辆），DyHead COCO的线性探测与全微调性能相当，但对于一些新颖领域的其他任务（例如，AerialDrone），差距较大。
